<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Taunt1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Taunt,</orth> subst. scoff, insulting mockery: <cit><quote>to stand at the t. of one who makes fritters of English,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.151" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 151</bibl></cit>. Usually in the plur. <cit><quote>--s:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 39</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.66" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 6, 66</bibl> <cit><quote>(give).</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.106" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 106</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.259" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 259</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 73</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>